@(3.B.1 = 1-11) @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“His food is set apart, his water is set apart, he eats the food offered (?) to him, he drinks the water offered (?) to him.”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see him who fell in battle? How does he fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“His father and mother are not there to hold his head, and his wife weeps.”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see him who ……? How does he fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“…… from his (?) hand …….”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see the spirit of him who has no funerary offerings? How does he fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“He eats the scraps and the crumbs tossed out in the street.”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see my little stillborn children who never knew existence? How do they fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“They play with a bucket of gold and silver, full of honey and ghee.”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see him who was set on fire?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“I did not see him. His spirit is not there. His smoke went up to the sky.”}



@h A third version from Urim (UET 6 60)

@(4.1 = 1-10) They returned to @wSN{Unug}, they returned to their city. He entered outfitted with tools and armaments, with an axe and a spear, and deposited them in his palace happily. Looking at the statue, the young men and women of @wSN{Unug} and the old men (?) and women of @wSN{Kulaba} rejoiced. As @wDN{Utu} came forth from his bedchamber, @wDN{Gilgameš} (?) raised his head and told them (?): @q[Gilgamec,]{“My father and my mother, drink clean water!”} Midday had hardly passed when they touched the statue's (?) crown.

@(4.11 = 11-16) @wDN{Gilgameš} threw himself down at the place of mourning, he threw himself down for nine days at the place of mourning. The young men and women of @wSN{Unug} and the old men (?) and women of @wSN{Kulaba} wept. As soon as he had said that, he repulsed the citizen of @wSN{Ŋirsu}. @q[Gilgamec,]{“My father and my mother, drink clean water!”}

@(4.17 = 17) Warrior @wDN{Gilgameš}, son of @wDN{Ninsumun}, sweet is your praise!



@h A version from Me-Turan


@(5.A.1 = 1-9) …… surrounded him. He carried …… and the spirits felt insulted (?) by him. He caused (?) …….

$ (1 line fragmentary)
He kissed his beloved wife, and hit his wife when he was angry with her. He kissed his beloved child, and hit his son when he was angry with him. He aroused an outcry and was detained in the nether world.

@(5.A.10 = 10-16) From that fateful day and for seven days his servant, @wPN{Enkidu}, did not come out from the nether world. The king was lamenting, crying bitterly: @q[Gilgamec,]{“My beloved servant, my faithful companion, my counsellor, has been seized in the nether world! @wDN{Namtar} did not seize him, the Asag did not seize him; but he was seized in the nether world. The @fsux{udug} of @wDN{Nergal} who …… did not seize him, but he was seized in the nether world. He did not fall in battle on the field of ……, but he was seized in the nether world.”}

@(5.A.17 = 17-24) He directed his steps on his own to @wTN{E-kur}, the temple of @wDN{Enlil}. Before @wDN{Enlil}, he ……: @q[Gilgamec,Enlil]{“My ball (?) fell down into the nether world, my mallet (?) fell down into @wGN{Ganzer}. But @wPN{Enkidu}, going down to retrieve them, my beloved servant, my faithful companion, my counsellor, was seized in the nether world. @wDN{Namtar} did not seize him, the Asag did not seize him, but he was seized in the nether world. …… did not seize him, but he was seized in the nether world.”}

