} .”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see him who had five sons? How does he fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“Like a good scribe he is indefatigable, he enters the palace easily.”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see him who had six sons? How does he fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“He is cheerful as a ploughman.”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see him who had seven sons? How does he fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“As a companion of the gods he sits on a throne and listens to judgments.”} @q[Gilgamec,Enkidu]{“Did you see him who had no heir? How does he fare?”} @q[Enkidu,Gilgamec]{“Like (?) …… he eats bread.”}

